  "response_text": "Here’s a great fruit-based snack that’s packed with antioxidants:\n\n**Dark Chocolate-Dipped Berries**\n\n**Why it works:**  \n- **Berries (blueberries, strawberries, raspberries, or blackberries)** are loaded with anthocyanins and vitamin C, which are powerful antioxidants.  \n- **Dark chocolate (70% cocoa or higher)** is rich in flavonoids, another class of antioxidants.  \n- The combination is simple, delicious, and far healthier than processed sweets.\n\n**How to make it:**  \n1. Wash and thoroughly dry a cup of mixed berries.  \n2. Melt 2–3 ounces of dark chocolate (use a double boiler or microwave in 15-second bursts).  \n3. Dip each berry halfway into the chocolate, then place on a parchment-lined tray.  \n4. Refrigerate for 15–20 minutes until the chocolate sets.  \n\n**Optional boost:** Sprinkle with a pinch of sea salt or unsweetened shredded coconut before the chocolate hardens.  \n\nThis snack provides fiber, vitamins, and a concentrated dose of antioxidants without added refined sugar (if you use high-quality dark chocolate). Enjoy in moderation—the chocolate adds calories, but the health benefits are real.",
